<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=104730669337886></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104730669337886><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=104730669337886>RE: CS/ID vs CA/LR</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=104730669337886#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13385><span id=Scholar>Neptunis</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>258 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 10th 10:05 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I forgot to add, there is a big write-up on Combat Stability on the Steel Warriors board.&nbsp;&nbsp;Consensus there is Combat Stability doesn't lower damage enough to be worth the AA's.  The only ones who argued CS over CA were trying to show how loosing damage from the damage shield so it was lowering the Tanks DPS to have high CA.<br><br>They have a bunch of parsers there and posted alot of numbers to back up their claim.  I'd recommend you look at their info and pull out the facts from the rest of the junk yourself.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 60 DE Gravelord</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=104732393439031></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104732393439031><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=104732393439031>RE: CS/ID vs CA/LR</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=104732393439031#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>262 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Mar 10th 2:52 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Im aware of the comments at the Steel Warriors.&nbsp;&nbsp;I was asking here to see if anyone else had any other ideas or comments or links, etc..<br><br>Also, you might want to re-examine those threads in closer detail.  The consensus on the thread(s) that I have read, some of which included some detailed parses, strongly hinted that CS/ID = CA/LR, which makes logical sense.  There appears little reason why VI would make one AA ability vastly superior to another for the same type of classes, for the same situation, at the same cost.<br><br>The general agreement for CA appears to be that you can avoid stuns and procs off the mobs from hits.  It has nothing to do with reducing damage received moreso than with CS.<br><br>The general agreement related to CS was a very slight reduction in overall damage received, higher DPS when combined with a DS, and a lower damage *spike*.  Personally, I dont like the work *spike*, as it actually increases the spike, but I think what they were meaning was a *shorter* damage *plateau*.<br><br>In any case, my view of it is that they are about equivalent.  Some people will swear by CA, others will swear by CS.  Determining which truly is better, however, is about as useful as debating with race is better.  There may be some variances, but, at the end of the day, nothing that is crazy advantageous.<br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
