	   <tr><td colspan=2>Personal opinion?&nbsp;&nbsp;Yeh I think Combat Agility is far superior for an SK to Natural Durability.  Combat Stability seems to be the weakest of the 3 though.<br><br>I put one point each into all 3 to start, the only one I say a real improvement in was Combat Agility.  I gained 80 HP's on Natural Durability, but when fighting with just me and a Cleric against the same MOBs in PoN, I went from 2 CHeals to a CHeal and a Divine Light heal when I got CA 1.  With CA 2 I dropped damage from the same MOBs to just needing 1 CHeal.  To me that's a huge difference, far above the 200 HP's I would have gotten from ND 2.  And since I don't tank Major MOBs for my Guild I really get better results from avoiding a few more blows with a better chance of FD working if I inadvertantly get agro during a fight.<br><br>Many will disagree with me.  The &quot;HP's = god&quot; group will definately find fault with this, but it works for me.  I'll spend alot of AA's before I ever get around to getting ND 3.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Neptunis Rex<br>lvl 60 DE Gravelord</td></tr>
